data.chText: 不同的；有区别的；有差异的
data.enText: not the same as sb/sth; not like sb/sth else

data.chText: 美国英语与英国英语有很大差异。
data.enText: American English is significantly different from British English.

data.chText: 这与我所习惯的大不相同。
data.enText: It's very different to what I'm used to.

data.chText: 他认为他与其他人没什么两样。
data.enText: He saw he was no different than anybody else.

data.chText: 现在同一年前不一样了。
data.enText: It's different now than it was a year ago.

data.chText: 人们常常对同一件事的叙述大为不同。
data.enText: People often give very different accounts of the same event.

data.chText: 我儿子邋遢极了，女儿也不比他强。
data.enText: My son's terribly untidy; my daughter's no different .

data.chText: 分别的；各别的；各种的
data.enText: separate and individual

data.chText: 她给我们提供了五种不同的蛋糕。
data.enText: She offered us five different kinds of cake.

data.chText: 这个节目介绍全国各地的风俗习惯。
data.enText: The programme was about customs in different parts of the country.

data.chText: 这些有多种颜色供选购。
data.enText: They are sold in many different colours.

data.chText: 我分别在三本词典里查找过。
data.enText: I looked it up in three different dictionaries.

data.chText: 不平常；与众不同；别致
data.enText: unusual; not like other people or things

data.chText: “你喜欢这出戏吗？”“哦，的确不同凡响！”
data.enText: ‘Did you enjoy the play?’ ‘Well, it was certainly different!’

data.chText: 男孩儿和女孩儿的表现可能不同。
data.enText: Boys and girls may behave differently.

data.chText: 雄鸟的头形有点特别。
data.enText: The male bird has a differently shaped head.
a different kettle of fish

data.chText: 另一码事；截然不同的人
data.enText: a completely different situation or person from the one previously mentioned
put a new/different complexion on sth

data.chText: 使形势改观
data.enText: to change the way that a situation appears
know different/otherwise

data.chText: 所知道的不是那么回事；所掌握的情况大不一样（或大相径庭）
data.enText: to have information or evidence that the opposite is true

data.chText: 他说他并不在乎批评家的评论，可我知道不是那么回事。
data.enText: He says he doesn't care about what the critics write, but I know different.
be another/a different matter

data.chText: 另外一回事；又是一回事；另当别论
data.enText: to be very different

data.chText: 我知道他们住在哪一地区，但能不能找到他们的住宅则是另外一回事了。
data.enText: I know which area they live in, but whether I can find their house is a different matter.
pull in different/opposite directions

data.chText: 目标迥异；各行其是
data.enText: to have different aims that cannot be achieved together without causing problems
tell a different story/tale

data.chText: 说的情况迥然不同；讲出来的是另一回事
data.enText: to give some information that is different from what you expect or have been told

data.text: different from ♦ different to ♦ different than

data.chText: different from在英国英语和北美英语中均为最通用的结构。different to亦用于英国英语：
data.enText: Different from is the most common structure in both BrE and NAmE . Different to is also used in BrE .

data.chText: 保罗与他的哥哥大不一样。
data.enText: Paul’s very different from/to his brother.

data.chText: 这次访问与上一次大不相同。
data.enText: This visit is very different from/to last time.

data.chText: 北美英语亦有different than的说法：
data.enText: In NAmE people also say different than .

data.chText: 你们的火车与我们的不一样。
data.enText: Your trains are different than ours.

data.chText: 你看上去与从前不一样了。
data.enText: You look different than before.

data.chText: 从句前亦可用different from（北美英语用different than）：
data.enText: Before a clause you can also use different from (and different than in NAmE ).
She looked different from what I’d expected.

data.chText: 她看上去与我想象的不一样。
data.enText: She looked different than (what) I’d expected.

simple_means.memory_skill: differ 不同 + ent 具有…性质的 → 不同的

ex.chText: 他们彼此的政治观点不同。
ex.enText: They hold different political views from each other.

ex.chText: 她的裙子和我的不一样。
ex.enText: Her dress is different to mine.

ex.chText: 汤姆和在德国时好像不一样了。
ex.enText: Tom seemed different than he did in Germany.

synonyms.bx: 强调事物之间的区别，侧重对比，常与介词 from 连用；英国英语口语中也常用 different to, 而美国英语中则用 different than。

ex.chText: 在这家公司，不同文化背景的人在一起工作。
ex.enText: People from diverse cultures work together in this company.

ex.chText: 这个男孩才5岁，但是他的兴趣非常广泛。
ex.enText: The boy is only 5 years old, but his interests are very diverse.

synonyms.bx: 语气较强，强调性质或种类不同，侧重表示区别显著。

ex.chText: 出于种种原因，他决定支持自己的对手。
ex.enText: He decided to support his rival for various reasons.

ex.chText: 有多种方法可以解决这个问题。
ex.enText: There are various ways to solve this problem.

synonyms.bx: 强调种类不同，通常作定语。

value.def: If two people or things are different, they are not like each other in one or more ways.

example.ex: London was different from most European capitals...
example.tran: 伦敦同大多数欧洲国家的首都都有所不同。

example.ex: If he'd attended music school, how might things have been different?...
example.tran: 如果他上过音乐学校，事情会有怎样的不同呢？

posc.def: In British English, people sometimes say that one thing is different to another. Some people consider this use to be incorrect.

example.ex: My approach is totally different to his.
example.tran: 我的方法和他的完全不同。

posc.def: People sometimes say that one thing is different than another. This use is often considered incorrect in British English, but it is acceptable in American English.

example.ex: We're not really any different than they are.
example.tran: 我们跟他们其实并没有什么不同。

example.ex: ...a style of advertising that's different than the rest of the country.
example.tran: 与该国其他地区的广告很不相同的广告风格
每个人的学习方式都不一样。

example.ex: They still get treated differently from almost every other contemporary British band...
example.tran: 他们所得到的待遇仍然与当代几乎所有其他英国乐队都不同。

example.ex: The skeleton consists of differently shaped bones held together by ligaments.
example.tran: 人体骨架是由依靠韧带连接的形状相异的骨头构成。

value.def: You use different to indicate that you are talking about two or more separate and distinct things of the same kind.

example.ex: Different countries specialised in different products...
example.tran: 不同国家专门生产不同的产品。

example.ex: The number of calories in different brands of drinks varies enormously.
example.tran: 不同牌子的饮料所含的卡路里数大不相同。

value.def: You can describe something as different when it is unusual and not like others of the same kind.

example.ex: This recipe is certainly interesting and different.
example.tran: 这种烹饪法的确很有意思而且与众不同。

value.tran: 不同寻常的;与众不同的

value.boxu_tran: 在英国英语中，有时会用 different to 来表示某物不同于另一物：You're different to what I imagined (你跟我想象的不同)。一些人认为该用法不正确，坚称应用 different from：We humans are different from all other species (我们人类不同于所有其他物种)。在美国英语中，可用 different than 来表示某物不同于另一物。该用法在英国英语中常被视为不正确，但当比较中涉及一个分句时，它有时是最简单可行的表达方式： I am no different than I was 50 years ago (我和 50 年前没有什么不同)。
value.boxu_usage: In British English, people sometimes say that one thing is different to another. You're different to what I imagined. Some people consider this use to be incorrect, and insist that you should say different from. We humans are different from all other species. In American English, you can say that one thing is different than another. This use is often considered incorrect in British English, but it is sometimes the simplest possibility when the comparison involves a clause. I am no different than I was 50 years ago.
